WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Today inshallah we're going to focus on how to deal with and what does it mean?

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:13.000
I want to talk to you about uh how to to navigate through it and how

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:21.000
to really face it and and then we're going to talk about patience and perseverance

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:29.000
and and and inshallah we're learning through how to take care of ourselves in calamities and times of hardship as we

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:35.000
all go through. So let's go through it inshallah.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:43.000
In Islam, there is a sixth pillar that every Muslim must believe in. It is called to believe in

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:52.000
it's good and it's bad. What is and what does it mean good and bad?

00:00:52.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Sometimes the word in the Quran appears in a different word. Sometimes it appears as and sometimes both of these words are the same thing.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:11.000
They're both synonymous. They go hand in hand together. But for those who want to become technical to know the difference

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:18.000
between and is the following is

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:26.000
literally means a final order a final decision a fixed in advance.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:34.000
It's usually when a judge makes a judgment and it's final. In Islam it means something that has been decided and ordered by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:40.000
for all his creations. whether it is in terms of its creation, destruction or

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:48.000
changes. Then we go to the word — ad means pre-measurement or set to a

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:56.000
certain amount and executed like rolled out, made to exist. Islamically, it is something that has been measured and set

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:04.000
at a certain amount since the beginning of time so that it follows Allah's knowledge which comes before everything.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:14.000
So is what will be and is how it will be in a very simple sentence. Just take this sentence.

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:21.000
You can say — and is the belief, the Muslim belief, that everything that

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:31.000
happens is pre-measured and predetermined by Allah and only Allah.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:43.000
Before he created creation — based on his infinite knowledge, his will, his power, his wisdom, his justice, and his mercy.

00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:49.000
So here are some other definitions. It's fate and destiny that is all from Allah.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:58.000
Fate and destiny is all determined and measured by Allah. Everything that happens is by Allah's will. Everything has been predetermined. Allah created

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:02.000
everything, decided everything about everything and determined its destiny.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:11.000
Everything that will ever be is written, willed, created, and known by Allah perfectly. Nothing happens without his will. And all of this happened

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:17.000
50,000 years before Allah created creation. That's in the authentic hadith. And there are many verses in the

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:41.000
Quran that talk about this. For example, Allah says in surah Al-Qamar: everything we have created in a precise measure and pre-ordainment.

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:55.000
Allah says in the Quran: everything we have created in a precise measure and pre-ordainment.

00:03:55.000 --> 00:04:06.000
And our command and matter is only but like the blink of an eye — meaning the end of time. When the end of time comes it is like the blink of an eye.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:13.000
It also means that whatever Allah wants to create or to happen, he only says "Be" and it is. We see another verse in the

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:21.000
Quran talking about predestination — Allah's decision. When he talks about the story of Jesus son of Mary, when he

00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:28.000
was born of a miraculous birth, the Christians later on said that he has a father who is God — he's a son of God.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:36.000
They said it was Joseph the carpenter who

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:43.000
either married Maryam or — God forbid — they say something else. But Allah answers them by

00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:56.000
saying — Allah says: That is Jesus son of Mary in truthful fact.

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:04.000
[Music]

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
[Laughter]

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:18.000
[Music]

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:26.000
Very easy and very simple. Allah says: that is Jesus son of Mary in truthful fact.

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:35.000
It is not befitting nor is it possible for Allah to beget a son. Far away is he from any imperfection.

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:45.000
When he decrees and decides a matter, he merely says "Be" and it is. What does it mean? It means that Isa was born without a father.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:53.000
People were very astonished — how? So Allah replies: he just says "Be" and it is.

00:05:53.000 --> 00:06:00.000
Had he been born a normal birth, nobody would be shocked or astonished. Allah wouldn't have to say "Be". It would be like everyone else. So it was a miracle.

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:10.000
So brothers and sisters, Allah decrees everything and says "Be" and it is. This is called Qadr — and once it's done, nothing can change it.

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:18.000
And predestination — fate, destiny, Allah's will — nothing happens without Allah's will. Qadr is good and

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:22.000
bad. What does it mean that there is good and bad?

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:28.000
First and foremost, brothers and sisters, we never attribute to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala anything bad.

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:34.000
Nothing bad comes from Allah. And you might say: then how is fate and destiny

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:43.000
good and bad? Yes. Bad is divided into two branches.

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:50.000
This is in the Quran and it's also in the sunnah. The first branch is bad things that have no benefit or wisdom

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:58.000
whatsoever — they're just plain evil. And there is no evil that comes from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala. No matter what you see in life, anything that looks bad to

00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:07.000
you, don't ever say that Allah decrees evil things. Evil only comes from people, not from Allah subhanahu wa

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:15.000
ta'ala. So what is the bad that comes from Allah? They are the ones that are mixed with a wisdom that comes out of

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:24.000
them. Allah created the good and he created the bad. The bad he created only because from the bad there comes good.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:26.000
Without some bad, there will be no good.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:32.000
And I'll give you an example — a scenario.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:38.000
A doctor, a surgeon who you trust.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:45.000
If you took your child who has got a severe problem that requires surgery

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:53.000
and you saw that surgeon cut your child open and you see all that blood coming

00:07:53.000 --> 00:08:02.000
out and the bones being cut and organs being replaced and stitching it up, giving painkillers, going through months of agony —

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:10.000
Will you still be grateful to that doctor or will you abuse the doctor?

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:18.000
You'd be grateful — to Allah first, then to the doctor. Thank you doctor for helping, because my son is going to heal inshallah.

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:23.000
But was there pain? Was there ugliness?

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:27.000
Was there some things that we see from our eyes as humans as bad?

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:34.000
Allah created pain. He created some things that to us look bad but from

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:42.000
them comes good. So when Allah says to believe in Qadr — that Allah pre-measures everything to happen whether it's good

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:49.000
or bad — it means that the bad is also good, but sometimes bad is a necessity. Do you understand?

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:56.000
Let's give another example. I always use this. When you learn how to walk as a baby,

00:08:56.000 --> 00:09:04.000
do you walk immediately without any pain, or do you have to fall sometimes? Some babies if you're not careful might get injured,

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:08.000
but they're learning eventually how to walk.

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:16.000
You would rather them fall a hundred times to eventually learn how to walk than not be able to walk all their life.

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:23.000
Nobody's going to focus on the minor harm. And by the way, anything that looks bad that Allah has decreed is

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:33.000
always temporary. It never stays for long. That's why Allah says in the Quran —

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:43.000
he repeats it twice — so that we can drill it in our heads: As a matter of fact, with hardship is always ease. As a matter of fact, with hardship is always ease.

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:51.000
Meaning the hardship which Allah allows to happen, there is always ease and goodness that's going to come out of it.

00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:58.000
What is your duty? Your duty is to assume of Allah your Lord positively.

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:06.000
When does evil come out? When you start to assume of your Lord negatively. Who created evil? You — by that assumption. That's when you live

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:21.000
in agony. Allah says in the Quran —

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:36.000
[Applause]

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:44.000
Allah describes certain people that when they're faced with calamities, they face it with negativity. They assume of Allah bad, and they give up and they turn away

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:52.000
from Allah. Allah says: there are people in the world who — when

00:10:52.000 --> 00:11:01.000
good comes their way — they're relaxed and satisfied. They stay where they are, relaxed, thinking "I'm all good." And when a calamity or something negative happens to them, they turn flat on their faces — meaning they turn against the world, they

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:09.000
blame everybody, they have fights with everyone, they blame Allah. Allah says: some of them worship Allah

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:17.000
their whole lives as if a person is walking on the edge of a cliff. Have you ever seen anyone walking on the edge of a cliff —

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:26.000
maybe on social media? — they're in danger. But the meaning of this verse is: when somebody's walking on the edge of a cliff, it means you're just on the edge.

00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:34.000
Meaning a little wind or breeze may make you fall. So Allah says there are some people who follow their religion just on the edge — they do the absolute

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:42.000
minimum — and any tiny little negative thing that happens in their life, immediately they lose the plot. Allah says there are people who worship Allah

00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:49.000
like that — not really fully into it — and then when a calamity befalls them they fall on their faces like a person walking on the edge of a cliff.

00:11:49.000 --> 00:12:01.000
This is the person who loses both the goodness in this world and the goodness of the hereafter. When we all understand that we are created in this world for a

00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:09.000
test, you will understand that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala told us this a long time ago — for those who read the Quran.

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:16.000
It's even in the Bible and the Torah that they also received.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:19.000
Everyone — let's have a look at what Allah said and what he told us about this life.

00:12:19.000 --> 00:12:28.000
It is in Al-Baqarah and

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:35.000
other surahs like it. You all know the story of when Allah created Adam and told the angels to bow

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:42.000
to Adam. Let's analyze it for a second.

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:49.000
In chapter 2:30, Allah says: "Just think —

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:57.000
when your Lord said to the angels: Lo, I am about to place a viceregent

00:12:57.000 --> 00:13:03.000
on earth." The angels said: "Oh Allah, will you place on it one who will spread mischief and shed blood

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:07.000
while we celebrate your glory and extol your holiness?" He said: "Surely I know what you do not know."

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:28.000
I don't know if people read that verse and think deeply about it — because in this is the answer to everything in our life. Listen carefully.

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:37.000
First of all — Malak. Angel in the Arabic language means message-bearer.

00:13:37.000 --> 00:13:45.000
Malak, plural Malaikah — message bearers — which means that angels are not abstract

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:59.000
depersonalized beings. They have a personality. They have a life.

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:08.000
They are not just forces that fly around. They are beings with a personality of their own and

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:16.000
they are employed by Allah subhana wa ta'ala for the administration of his universe. They are his faithful servants. So they have a personality and

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:24.000
they can choose to obey or disobey — contrary to what some people say, that angels have no free will. Actually

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:33.000
they do have free will. Angels have free will but what they don't have is desires and temptations.

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:42.000
They don't have those desires that humans have. It's the

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:49.000
desires that make us go astray — and that is why they are obedient and they choose to obey Allah. So he said: I am placing a

00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:58.000
viceregent on earth. A viceregent is a deputy —

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:04.000
a person who acts in the place of a ruler or a governor or a sovereign.

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:12.000
Who is that person whom Allah is going to place on earth as a deputy — a person who acts in the place of a ruler? The ruler is Allah.

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:16.000
Who is he placing? You and me — as what?

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:25.000
We are the deputies, the ones who act under the rule of Allah, on behalf of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala. We have

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:30.000
certain duties and powers in this life.

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:39.000
That's why Allah said in the Quran: we have certainly honored the children of Adam.

00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:45.000
Allah honored us — and that is why Allah said to the angels: bow to Adam.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:16:01.000
Now they said to him — not opposing him, they just asked: what's the wisdom behind making a new creation on earth — a viceregent, someone who's a deputy of you on earth?

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:09.000
I mean, if you're after glorifying you and everything to be pure — here we are. We're already pure, our Lord. We

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:16.000
pray to you. We glorify your name. We're pure. You don't see us shedding blood. You don't see us

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:27.000
doing corruption. If that's what you want, our Lord — I'm just paraphrasing what the angels mean — we're here. We're already doing that.

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:30.000
Why would there need to be someone else?

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:36.000
Where's the gap? Are we missing something? Have we done something wrong?

00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:44.000
If you realize, brothers and sisters, the angels lacked knowledge about what Allah subhana wa ta'ala knows.

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:54.000
They thought that Allah wants people to always worship him and be absolutely pure with no problems.

00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:58.000
But they misunderstood. Who is Allah? I'll give you an example.

00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:06.000
Among Allah's names and attributes is Al-Adl — the Just.

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:10.000
How is Allah subhana wa ta'ala going to manifest this attribute of his without having

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:26.000
vices — good and bad — and justice? Allah is the Merciful. Mercy is applied when

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:33.000
somebody deserves to be punished. How is mercy going to be manifested in the world? Allah is the

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:40.000
Creator. How is he the Creator when he's not creating? So it's far beyond our minds. But Allah subhana wa ta'ala —

00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:48.000
he created these people — us — with free will, with desires, with temptations, with

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:56.000
ability and knowledge that the angels don't have. Allah honored us in this way. Angels, because of their

00:17:56.000 --> 00:18:04.000
lack of desire, didn't really understand free will. What does it mean to have free will? It means they didn't understand it because they didn't have

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:12.000
desires and temptations. When you have desires and temptations, they pull you towards the wrong — so now you have to make decisions. Do you

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:21.000
understand? Without desires and temptations, decisions are easy — you already know where you're going naturally. But when you have a vice

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:30.000
that's pulling you, you have to make a decision against it. And this is where your rank rises — this is how you get closer to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:38.000
The person who's already naturally inclined to good — and the person who has a choice between tough times,

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:48.000
challenging times and easy times, and chooses to face the challenges and rise — the second is greater to Allah.

00:18:48.000 --> 00:18:57.000
A person who struggles and strives against odds to please Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala while they go through pain is higher in the eyes of Allah. And all of

00:18:57.000 --> 00:19:06.000
us are like that inshallah. It's up to our choice. It's only a short time then we return back to Allah — no more challenges, no more tests.

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:13.000
So from the beginning Allah said: I am creating those who will represent my laws in this earth on behalf of me.

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:21.000
In other words, that's what Allah is saying. So this world is not a paradise for us.

00:19:21.000 --> 00:19:23.000
Allah is saying: you have to work in it.

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:29.000
You have to defend each other, protect each other, uphold the justice. Don't wait for me to bring down the angels to

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:37.000
you. You are representatives. So go and uphold it — strive and struggle —

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:45.000
and I will be with you, watching over you all the way. And nothing will go in vain.

00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:52.000
Whether it's death, whether it's sickness, whether it's hardship, whether it's loss of wealth, loss of lives, loss of

00:19:52.000 --> 00:20:01.000
anything. The Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam told us in a hadith in Muslim: there is nothing that a Muslim receives — whether it be worry,

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:09.000
anxiety, fear, hurt from someone's hurtful words, or anything like that — even the prick of

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:16.000
a needle — except that Allah compensates that person by forgiving their past sins

00:20:16.000 --> 00:20:24.000
and raising their ranks. Nothing goes in vain, brothers and sisters. And when someone can put that in their mind, suddenly life

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:31.000
becomes so sweet. I'll give you an example.

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:36.000
Let's say that you had a business opportunity and you were going to make a lot of money — that's what you thought.

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:43.000
And then the opportunity passed you and you said: "Oh no, another person took it. They made millions. I could have

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:52.000
made millions." Allah replies to you in the Quran: It is so that

00:20:52.000 --> 00:21:01.000
you do not despair over what passed you, and do not boast and go overboard

00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:08.000
over the blessings that came your way. For Allah does not like every boaster or arrogant,

00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:15.000
ungrateful person. So Qadr comes and tells you: listen, if it passed you — alhamdulillah — this

00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:24.000
was what Allah had written for you. If you got it — say alhamdulillah and don't boast. Just be normal. For you are in a

00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:32.000
test in this life. Everybody's going to leave everything behind anyway — except their good deeds and bad deeds — those they'll take with them.

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:40.000
Now the story of the angels: Allah taught Adam the names of everything. Gave him knowledge. And then

00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:49.000
he said to the angels: "Tell me the names of all these things." Now there are angels that know everything about climate, angels that

00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:57.000
know about gravity, angels about fire, angels about water. Each one's got their position, but their knowledge is only in their expertise. Now Allah taught Adam the

00:21:57.000 --> 00:22:05.000
names of everything. So he became an all-rounder. Allah says to the angels: "Tell me the names of all these things

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:14.000
collectively." Angels individually didn't know. But

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:22.000
Adam was able to say them collectively — which means that Allah created the human being to have an intellect to learn. And through knowledge you become a deputy. You represent Allah's rule on

00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:36.000
earth. But you need resources. You need help. You need knowledge. The angels were dedicated to one or two things. The human beings have many

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:44.000
tasks. When you have many tasks, you are more important. That's why you honor people who have a more responsible job. That's how you rise.

00:22:44.000 --> 00:22:55.000
A person who just worries about what makes them happy in life without contributing — they're not important. They become a burden on community and society.

00:22:55.000 --> 00:23:04.000
Not important. So that's how Allah made us. And when the angels said: "Oh our Lord, glory to you. We have no

00:23:04.000 --> 00:23:15.000
knowledge except what you gave us." Allah then replied to them.

00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:24.000
He said to Adam: "Tell them all the names." And then he said to the angels: "Didn't I tell you that I know that which you do

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:33.000
not know, oh angels?" What's Allah telling them? Remember the question they asked: oh our Lord, would you place on earth one who would shed blood and

00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:40.000
spread corruption while we glorify you already? So Allah says: I know that which you do not know. Meaning — I know in

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:48.000
this creation and the reason why I have created them. And I do know that there will be some shedding of blood and corruption. Yet there are things that

00:23:48.000 --> 00:23:56.000
you, oh angels, can never conceive or comprehend even if I told you. I know that which you do not know. So the

00:23:56.000 --> 00:24:03.000
angels then accepted it wholeheartedly and said: "Our Lord, we only know what you taught us. We submit — and we'll even make dua for your creatures."

00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:09.000
And the angels do make dua for us. It's in the Quran.

00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:12.000
They seek forgiveness for those who are on earth.

00:24:12.000 --> 00:24:17.000
So brothers and sisters — why did I say this story?

00:24:17.000 --> 00:24:26.000
Because you know how the angels didn't know everything. They jumped to conclusions. The angels jumped to a conclusion and they thought that Allah

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:35.000
wanted this — but Allah told them: "No, no, no. There's a lot you don't know about. And if I told you, you're not going to get it. So how about you just take me as your Lord —

00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:42.000
be angels as you are and worship me and just trust me." They said: "Of course — forever." What does it mean

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:47.000
to us as humans? It means the same thing, brothers and sisters.

00:24:47.000 --> 00:24:56.000
Things that happen in our life — whether they look good or look bad. Number one: don't assume you know what Allah wants. You

00:24:56.000 --> 00:25:04.000
don't know. Number two: assume of Allah positively — that there is something good coming out of it. Assume that Allah has a plan for you, a forgiveness from

00:25:04.000 --> 00:25:13.000
you. And if it happens and you don't understand why — persevere through it and know that Allah will not let anything go in vain. He will reward you

00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:22.000
or forgive you and it will all be counted for you as an investment for your hereafter. To the point where the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam said in one authentic hadith: on the

00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:29.000
Day of Judgment, there will be people who will look at other people who had gone through so much struggle and pain in this world. And they themselves

00:25:29.000 --> 00:25:37.000
had not gone through the same torture. And when they see what rank Allah has given those who suffered — the amount of rewards and pleasure that Allah has

00:25:37.000 --> 00:25:46.000
given them because of their patience and perseverance with calamities — the people who had lived in luxury will say: we wish we could go back to earth so that we

00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:54.000
could be cut into pieces — so that we

00:25:54.000 --> 00:26:01.000
could be successful as these people are successful. But see — on the Day of Judgment that becomes a privilege.

00:26:01.000 --> 00:26:10.000
Here it looks terrible and horrific. And nobody should go through it. But Allah knows who would have passed it and who would not. And

00:26:10.000 --> 00:26:18.000
so Allah doesn't give everybody the same tests and trials. Some people go through mental trials — some psychological, some emotional. Some go through

00:26:18.000 --> 00:26:27.000
relationship breakups. Some go through money problems, food problems, loss of lives, sickness, death, losses

00:26:27.000 --> 00:26:33.000
of some other sort — losing your job, problems in your life.

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:40.000
Sometimes it's because of yourself as well. But then Allah says to you: okay, you still have a chance. Get out of it.

00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:44.000
Fix yourself and the road can come back.

00:26:44.000 --> 00:26:53.000
So brothers and sisters, this life is built on tests and trials and calamities. Allah never promised you a paradise here. This is not it.

00:26:53.000 --> 00:27:02.000
This is not it. Until you get that out of your head, you won't find the peace and contentment you're looking for.

00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:11.000
One person said to me: "Imagine that you're on the Day of Judgment watching yourself in a live movie — and you are the hero of that movie. The big star —

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:19.000
watching yourself wake up from bed, going to sleep, praying fajr or missing it, going

00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:26.000
here, going there, going to school, going to work, coming back, meeting with your parents, cousins, relatives, spouse, children — going to work,

00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:35.000
earning your money, eating, drinking, spending time with friends, in your car, what you're listening to. Imagine you're watching yourself every single second.

00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:44.000
And then he said to me: if you're looking at yourself and you see you doing something good — like praying — and you finish and you say alhamdulillah — and you

00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:52.000
want yourself to keep going because you see your rank rising — and then suddenly you see yourself get up quickly and just start doing other things. What

00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:59.000
would you want to do? If you're looking at yourself like that, you'd say: oh my God, look — there was somebody in need. You could have given charity. Just take your phone and give a

00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:06.000
charity. Or maybe over there — your mother needed some help, or your father — go and help them. Or that person you're upset with — you could have said: hey, let's

00:28:06.000 --> 00:28:14.000
make it up. The idea is: you will look back at yourself and say — I wish I could go back so that I could give

00:28:14.000 --> 00:28:22.000
more in charity and good deeds and change the fate of my eternity. So a Muslim lives their life with the

00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:31.000
hereafter in mind. Brothers and sisters — with Qadr — let's investigate very quickly the story in the Quran:

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:38.000
Musa, alayhis salam, went — and Allah said to him: there is a man

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:45.000
whom we have given knowledge more than you.

00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:52.000
We have given this particular man knowledge from us — meaning it is not natural knowledge.

00:28:52.000 --> 00:29:01.000
It's not your common knowledge that fits with the laws of this world. We have given him some special

00:29:01.000 --> 00:29:10.000
knowledge which we didn't give to other people. So Musa alayhis salam said: "Oh my Lord, show me where he is so I may go and learn from him." Allah told him where to

00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:28.000
find him. Cutting the story short — he went with his apprentice and found the man. It is said that his name was Al-Khodr. And he said to him:

00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:35.000
"Would you allow me to follow you so that you may teach me of what you have been taught of guidance and goodness?"

00:29:35.000 --> 00:29:43.000
The man did not hesitate and immediately shot back with a reply.

00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:51.000
He said: "You will not be able to be patient with me." He did not ask him his name. He didn't even say salam. Just: "Can I follow

00:29:51.000 --> 00:30:02.000
you?" The man looks at him and says: "You can't be patient." Musa got shocked and said:

00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:09.000
"You will find me, if Allah wills, very patient and persevering, and I won't disobey you in anything." He said:

00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:17.000
"Okay. If you're going to follow me, then don't ask me about a

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:31.000
single thing that I do — until I decide to tell you." Just like that — straight to business. He said: "Very well."

00:30:31.000 --> 00:30:40.000
They entered — they were going to cross the sea and they found two brothers from a poor family

00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:47.000
who had a boat which they used for their business — going from land to land. They said: "Can

00:30:47.000 --> 00:30:57.000
you give us a lift to the next land?" So they gave him a lift, were very kind to them — gave them food, shelter, water. And they gave them a room at the bottom of the deck.

00:30:57.000 --> 00:31:06.000
When they went underneath, Al-Khodr took an axe and started to break and ruin the core of the ship.

00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:15.000
Musa alayhis salam immediately jumped and said: "How could you wreck their ship when they did so much good for us?" And Al-Khodr immediately said

00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:23.000
to him: "Didn't I tell you, you will not be able to be patient with me?" And Musa remembered — it hadn't been even a day.

00:31:23.000 --> 00:31:33.000
He remembered immediately and said: "Please don't hold me

00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:42.000
accountable for what I forgot. Don't lecture me. Just let me go — I understood my lesson."

00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:51.000
So they went until they reached a young boy — maybe 9, 10 years old. Al-Khodr comes

00:31:51.000 --> 00:32:00.000
up to him and kills him. Musa explodes:

00:32:00.000 --> 00:32:08.000
"Have you killed a soul unjustly? You've done something terribly outrageous."

00:32:08.000 --> 00:32:20.000
Al-Khodr said: "Didn't I say you will not be patient with me?" And Musa was also getting impatient with Al-Khodr's impatience response.

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:29.000
Musa said: if

00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:37.000
I ask you about anything after now, you can kick me out. I've got no more excuses. They went — they entered into a little

00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:44.000
town and the townspeople were horrible to them. They abused them, swore at them, spat at them, gave them no food. They were

00:32:44.000 --> 00:32:51.000
very tired — it was a norm to give travellers food — and they kicked them out. On their way out they saw a

00:32:51.000 --> 00:32:55.000
wall that was being built — part of a building.

00:32:55.000 --> 00:33:03.000
So Al-Khodr goes and starts helping these evil people to construct the wall.

00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:10.000
Musa, after they finish helping, says: you know, you could have taken some

00:33:10.000 --> 00:33:22.000
money or food off them just for the help. He said: that's it — we depart from here.

00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:32.000
You have finished all your excuses. Musa said: okay, that's it — I wasn't patient enough.

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:37.000
So Al-Khodr said: but I will tell you the meanings of these three things before you go.

00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:46.000
As for the ship — that belonged to the poor people who worked on the sea. They were good people. But on their route

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:52.000
which they have to travel, there is a king that was replacing another king and he was very evil — he was

00:33:52.000 --> 00:34:00.000
taking every ship that looked good from families. So I wanted to make it look damaged so the king would leave them alone and they could continue on their journey.

00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:10.000
As for the boy — he was going to grow up and be a tyrant, an evil person to his parents. And his parents are good righteous people — his mother and

00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:26.000
father. So your Lord wanted to replace that child with a better child for them — one who would grow up to be righteous. Now Allah does not force

00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:31.000
people to be righteous, brothers and sisters. He knows what you're going to become. He doesn't make you do things.

00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:38.000
Some people come to me and say: "Sheikh, ask Allah to guide me to pray, ask Allah to guide me to wear the

00:34:38.000 --> 00:34:48.000
hijab, ask Allah to guide me so I may be able to fast." I say: that's not really the right dua.

00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:55.000
Guidance means that Allah lets you see what's

00:34:55.000 --> 00:35:03.000
right from wrong. The rest is up to you — you have to follow or not. Allah doesn't put a holy spirit in you.

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:12.000
That's what some people believe — that some spirit goes inside of you and suddenly you're enlightened. Doesn't happen that way.

00:35:12.000 --> 00:35:14.000
You are all alhamdulillah already enlightened. It's

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:30.000
like giving someone a map when they're lost and saying: take this map and go in that direction. If you keep following that map, you will get there. But if you don't trust

00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:35.000
the one who gave it — or you say "nah, stuff it" — you're going to get lost. Allah gave us the map.

00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:41.000
That's called hidayah. Hidayah is not some spirit that comes into you.

00:35:41.000 --> 00:35:48.000
The sky will not open up for you. The Quran is with you — you've already been guided. So Allah does not force people

00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:56.000
to repent. He does not force people to become religious. He doesn't force people to do the right thing. He already gave you the ability — just as you can do the

00:35:56.000 --> 00:36:03.000
wrong thing. So Allah does not make you do the wrong thing. Allah tells us then: he replaced that child for Allah

00:36:03.000 --> 00:36:12.000
to give better in its place — and all four of them end up in paradise. As for the wall — I helped them build it.

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:21.000
Truly they were evil — but that wall belonged to two orphans. And those orphans' seventh great-grandfather was a righteous man. So Allah wanted to look after his generation — all the way

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:30.000
down — so long as they are righteous. Which means: if you're righteous and your children are righteous, Allah will keep looking after your progeny till the hundredth generation. Subhan Allah. He said: underneath

00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:38.000
that wall there was a treasure. And those evil people were about to find it — if they saw it, they were going to take it off the orphans. And the orphans would not be able to use their treasure to look after themselves.

00:36:38.000 --> 00:36:47.000
So Allah wanted them to grow up — when they're strong enough so that they can take their own treasure out. He said: I had to

00:36:47.000 --> 00:36:54.000
help them — and I didn't want to say anything to those people. And then he says: I did not do this out of my own

00:36:54.000 --> 00:37:00.000
decision. Allah told me to do it. So we don't go ahead, brothers and sisters, and start doing things on this basis.

00:37:00.000 --> 00:37:09.000
Allah told him to do it. But the moral of the story, brothers and sisters, is: Allah is giving us an example using one of the greatest prophets and

00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:18.000
messengers in the world — Musa, alayhis salam. The one whom Allah spoke to at Mount Sinai. The receiver of the Torah. One of the five greatest prophets in

00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:25.000
Islam. Allah showed us that even he — in the time of really strong

00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:31.000
calamities and tests — was not successful. He could not be patient enough. So Allah gives everyone tests at their

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:38.000
level. In other words — had Musa known why Al-Khodr was doing what he did, he

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:46.000
would have been okay with it. But Allah is testing our patience — not giving us the answers. Because it is in your

00:37:46.000 --> 00:37:53.000
perseverance where your level rises. Can you imagine all the teachers giving you the answers to your exam? You become

00:37:53.000 --> 00:38:01.000
a doctor — you're going to hurt people.

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:04.000
A person studying to be a scholar — if you cheat and get all the answers, you'll misguide people. You get your license as

00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:12.000
a builder — next minute everyone's under the rubble.

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:24.000
Do you understand? And same with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala. Until we understand this brothers and sisters, we are not going to be able to face

00:38:24.000 --> 00:38:28.000
calamities with perseverance and patience.

00:38:28.000 --> 00:38:34.000
Finally, Allah says in the Quran —

00:38:34.000 --> 00:38:49.000
[Music]

00:38:49.000 --> 00:39:03.000
[Music]

00:39:03.000 --> 00:39:09.000
We will surely try you and test you and put you through calamities.

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:12.000
A little bit of fear — sometimes you're going to be afraid.

00:39:12.000 --> 00:39:16.000
You're going to be hungry. Sometimes you're going to lose some wealth.

00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:26.000
Sometimes you're going to lose loved ones. Death. And sometimes you lose luxuries and opportunities.

00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:34.000
Allah says: give the best news to those who persevere and are patient. The ones who when a calamity befalls them, they

00:39:34.000 --> 00:39:42.000
immediately say: to Allah we belong and to him we are going to return. The ayah continues: these are the

00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:49.000
people whom no harm or fear is going to be upon them on the Day of Judgment, and the angels will pray for them. Brothers

00:39:49.000 --> 00:39:55.000
and sisters — patience is an act of worship which many people have forgotten.

00:39:55.000 --> 00:40:02.000
It's called Sabr — taken from the prickly pear tree.

00:40:02.000 --> 00:40:09.000
Have you seen the prickly pear?

00:40:09.000 --> 00:40:30.000
Prickly pear. It's a nasty tree — it's got so many prickles on it. And to be able to get through all the prickles and the sharpened thorns —

00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:37.000
guess what you get out of it? A sweet, tasty fruit of different colors.

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:38.000
But you have to get through the thorns.

00:40:38.000 --> 00:40:47.000
You've got to be patient and careful and persevere — and then you'll get to the sweetness. Imagine life like that prickly pear. You need to get through

00:40:47.000 --> 00:40:57.000
the thorns and eventually you'll get to the sweetness inshallah. And I finish by saying: patience has three types.

00:40:57.000 --> 00:41:05.000
Not one — three. The highest one. The first type of patience we need is

00:41:05.000 --> 00:41:15.000
patience in worship and fulfilling the commands of Allah. That is the first and highest — because that requires patience.

00:41:15.000 --> 00:41:23.000
Musa alayhis salam had to be patient. We have to be patient with our salah, with our fasting, with our values, with

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:30.000
our morals, with our emotions, with our anger, with our mouths, with our hands, with our treatment of others, with our money. We all have to be

00:41:30.000 --> 00:41:38.000
patient. That is the highest rank — to be patient and persevere in the commands of Allah. As Allah says:

00:41:38.000 --> 00:41:45.000
worship your Lord until death comes to you.

00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:52.000
Command your family and teach them salah — and be patient with worship. The second level of patience is the opposite: to

00:41:52.000 --> 00:42:00.000
persevere and be patient and work hard and wrestle against doing sins —

00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:04.000
especially major sins. If minor sins just come by — so long as you do good deeds, it'll wipe them away. But don't insist on continuing with sins.

00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:19.000
So strive against sins as much as you can. Fight with them and wrestle — sins in your actions, sins in your

00:42:19.000 --> 00:42:27.000
words, sins in your eyes, sins in your ears, sins in your earning and spending, sins in your relationships. Strive to your best. And

00:42:27.000 --> 00:42:32.000
the way to strive is: if you fall, you repent. I'm going to repent. I'm going to try again. Repent, try again.

00:42:32.000 --> 00:42:40.000
But never ever give up. Patience against sins means you don't give up. You don't say: "I've missed so many prayers.

00:42:40.000 --> 00:42:49.000
I've done so many haram things. I used to do drugs. I've been a really bad person. I've got bad relationships. I've lost my family. I am a loser —

00:42:49.000 --> 00:42:56.000
I'm going to hellfire. Forget it." That is the shaytan telling you: "Don't come back to Allah." And Allah calls you

00:42:56.000 --> 00:43:04.000
again and again in the Quran: "Oh you who have burdened yourselves —

00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:11.000
thinking you have no more return because of your sins and

00:43:11.000 --> 00:43:18.000
bad deeds — do not give up from the mercy and forgiveness of Allah. Allah forgives all sins." So that's the second type of patience. And the last one —

00:43:18.000 --> 00:43:25.000
everybody knows this one. And that's what most people go through. It is when tragedies and

00:43:25.000 --> 00:43:34.000
calamities come your way. Any kind of tragedy, any kind of calamity — whatever it may be.

00:43:34.000 --> 00:43:39.000
What do you do with this patience? You hold yourself together.

00:43:39.000 --> 00:43:47.000
It doesn't mean you're not going to go through pain. It doesn't mean it's going to be easy. No — hold yourself together until you get past it.

00:43:47.000 --> 00:43:56.000
What does it mean to hold yourself together? It means: don't resort to immoral acts or give up on Allah. Hold yourself

00:43:56.000 --> 00:44:04.000
together. Hold in there. Even if you do not understand it — even if you cannot find closure — even if you cannot find a

00:44:04.000 --> 00:44:13.000
solution — hold in there. Do what you can. Ask Allah. Make dua. Keep going. Seek help. Get medical help if

00:44:13.000 --> 00:44:21.000
you need it. Use all the resources that you have — and don't give up and say "I am in ruins. I'm gone."

00:44:21.000 --> 00:44:28.000
Keep going. May Allah bless you, my brothers and sisters. It's now time for salah. Next week inshallah we'll continue.

00:44:28.000 --> 00:44:36.000
I'm not sure what the topic is, but I hope inshallah tonight we learned something beneficial. May Allah bless

00:44:36.000 --> 00:44:41.000
you and reward you. And lastly, we'll make a dua.

00:44:41.000 --> 00:44:49.000
For Palestine — oh Allah, give victory to our brothers in Palestine and change their state from fear to security, from hardship to ease. Oh Allah, protect

00:44:49.000 --> 00:44:57.000
them. Oh Allah, bless them. Oh Allah, relieve them from their hardship. Oh Allah, open the road to goodness for all of them. Oh Allah, return their rights

00:44:57.000 --> 00:45:02.000
to them and their property and their lands. Oh Allah, return the Muslims to your deen.

00:45:02.000 --> 00:45:06.000
Oh Allah, forgive us for our shortcomings and accept our dua.

